participant_b.entity_text: polypeptide receptor activator of nuclear factor-kappaB ligand

verbose_text: When a bone is fractured, the release of proinflammatory cytokines including tumor necrosis factor-alpha and interleukin-1beta leads to increased expression of the polypeptide receptor activator of nuclear factor-kappaB ligand (RANKL) from any of a number of local cell types.
evidence: expression of the polypeptide receptor activator of nuclear factor-kappaB ligand
